items.title: Home blood pressure monitoring for hypertension best combined with intensive support
items.summary: People who monitor their own blood pressure at home are most likely to see a benefit if they combine it with individually tailored intensive support, according to a new systematic literature review and meta-analysis.

alternate.title: Home blood pressure monitoring for hypertension best combined with intensive support

items.title: Screening for cervical abnormalities in women offered HPV vaccination
items.summary: Human papillomavirus (HPV) testing detects a higher number of precancerous cervical lesions than cytology-based Pap smears in a female population including a proportion offered HPV vaccination, according to a new study.

alternate.title: Screening for cervical abnormalities in women offered HPV vaccination

items.title: What web browsers and proteins have in common
items.summary: The discovery of a previously overlooked site on protein molecules may solve a mystery about how proteins are able to carry out specialized functions in living cells.

alternate.title: What web browsers and proteins have in common

items.title: Groundbreaking investigative effort identifies gonorrhea vaccine candidates
items.summary: Researchers have identified a pair of proteins that show promise as the basis for a gonorrhea vaccine.

alternate.title: Groundbreaking investigative effort identifies gonorrhea vaccine candidates

items.title: Management studies: Dishonesty shift
items.summary: Lying comes more easily to people in teams: Behavioral scientists have shown in an experimental study why groups are more likely to behave unethically than individuals.

items.title: A study switches from genetic to metabolic analysis to reconstitute evolutionary process
items.summary: A new method for analyzing a living being chemical compositions is tested in Andean plants and attest the genesis of species by means of geographic isolation. Scientists analyzed chemical compounds which express specific biogeographic trends in the evolutionary process, validating a Smithsonian hypothesis on the evolution of the genus Espeletia in the process.

alternate.title: A study switches from genetic to metabolic analysis to reconstitute evolutionary process
